{"title_page": "Kevin Ford (producer)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = non_performing_personnel\n| death_date       = \n| module2          = \n| module           = \n| embed            = \n| past_members     = \n| current_members  = \n| website          = \n| associated_acts  = [[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]]\n| label            = {{hlist|[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]|[[Spinnin' Records|Spinnin']]|[[Warner Music|Warner]]}}\n| years_active     = 2003\u2013present\n| instrument       = {{hlist|[[Sampler (musical instrument)|Sampler]]|vocals}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Producer|singer}}\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Dance-pop]]|[[Electronic dance music|EDM]]}}\n| death_place      = \n| origin           = [[Calabasas, California]]\n| honorific_prefix = \n| birth_place      = United States\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1992|8|7}}\n| alias            = KEVI\n| birth_name       = \n| native_name_lang = \n| native_name      = \n| caption          = \n| alt              = \n| landscape        = \n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| image            = \n| honorific_suffix = \n| name             = Kevin Ford\n| module3          = \n}}\n\n'''Kevin Ford''' (born August 7, 1992), also known by his stage name '''KEVI''', is an American producer and singer. He became famous as a member of the DJ trio [[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]] alongside Matthew Russell and [[Trevor Dahl]]. They gained international success with their single \"[[Sex (Cheat Codes and Kris Kross Amsterdam song)|Sex]]\" and are from Los Angeles, California.\n\n== Early life ==\nKevin Ford was born on August 7, 1992 in the United States. One year after Trevor Dahl began his career, he and Matthew Russell formed [[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]], an [[electronic dance music]] trio. He is originally from [[Calabasas, California]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ca.gov/|title=www.ca.gov {{!}} California State Portal|website=www.ca.gov|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref> He is old friends with [[Justin Bieber]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.justinbiebermusic.com/|title=Justin Bieber \u2013 Home |website=justinbiebermusic.com|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n[[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]]' hit song \"[[Sex (Cheat Codes and Kris Kross Amsterdam song)|Sex]]\" went ARIA Platinum as well as BPI Gold and peaked at number two on [[Norway]] and [[Swedish people|Swedish]] singles chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref> [[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]]' 2017 hit \"[[No Promises (Cheat Codes song)|No Promises]]\" featured [[Demi Lovato]].\n\n== Discography ==\n''See also: [[Cheat Codes (DJs)#Discography]]''\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ford, Kevin}}\n[[Category:Atlantic Records artists]]\n[[Category:Dance-pop musicians]]\n[[Category:Electronic dance music musicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Spinnin' Records artists]]\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n\n\n{{Music-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = non_performing_personnel\n| death_date       = \n| module2          = \n| module           = \n| embed            = \n| past_members     = \n| current_members  = \n| website          = \n| associated_acts  = [[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]]\n| label            = {{hlist|[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]|[[Spinnin' Records|Spinnin']]|[[Warner Music|Warner]]}}\n| years_active     = 2003\u2013present\n| instrument       = {{hlist|[[Sampler (musical instrument)|Sampler]]|vocals}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Producer|singer}}\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Dance-pop]]|[[Electronic dance music|EDM]]}}\n| death_place      = \n| origin           = [[Calabasas, California]]\n| honorific_prefix = \n| birth_place      = United States\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1992|8|7}}\n| alias            = KEVI\n| birth_name       = \n| native_name_lang = \n| native_name      = \n| caption          = \n| alt              = \n| landscape        = \n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| image            = \n| honorific_suffix = \n| name             = Kevin Ford\n| module3          = \n}}\n\n'''Kevin Ford''' (born August 7, 1992), also known by his stage name '''KEVI''', is an American producer and singer. He became famous as a member of the DJ trio [[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]] alongside Matthew Russell and [[Trevor Dahl]]. They gained international success with their single \"[[Sex (Cheat Codes and Kris Kross Amsterdam song)|Sex]]\" and are from Los Angeles, California.\n\n== Early life ==\nKevin Ford was born on August 7, 1992 in the United States. One year after Trevor Dahl began his career, he and Matthew Russell formed [[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]], an [[electronic dance music]] trio. He is originally from [[Calabasas, California]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ca.gov/|title=www.ca.gov {{!}} California State Portal|website=www.ca.gov|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref> He is old friends with [[Justin Bieber]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.justinbiebermusic.com/|title=Justin Bieber \u2013 Home |website=justinbiebermusic.com|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n[[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]]' hit song \"[[Sex (Cheat Codes and Kris Kross Amsterdam song)|Sex]]\" went ARIA Platinum as well as BPI Gold and peaked at number two on [[Norway]] and [[Swedish people|Swedish]] singles chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref> [[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]]' 2017 hit \"[[No Promises (Cheat Codes song)|No Promises]]\" featured [[Demi Lovato]].\n\n